<TITLE> Sadrul Amin, Nimchandra Bhowmik face arrest orders </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 13 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court Thursday issued orders to arrest Dhaka University professors Sadrul Amin and Nimchandra Bhowmik. The court also ordered confiscation of their property. The Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court for Dhaka also issued arrest warrants against 13 students of the same university. Sadrul Amin is the president of the Dhaka University Teachers Association and Nimchandra Bhowmik is the provost of Jagannath Hall. The arrest orders have been issued over violent student protests at DU in August. Dhaka metropolitan magistrate SM Ferdous Ahmed issued the arrest warrants and confiscation order after accepting the chargesheets. The students, who face warrants, are HM Qamrul Hasan Kachi, Md Nazrul Islam Russell, Adeeb Hassan, Hasan Mamoon, Saiful Islam Firoz, M Shamsul Kabir Rahat, Mritul Anwar, Rifaat Hossain Ziku, Rokonuzzaman Talukdar Babu, Qamruzzaman, Tanzin Chowdhury Lily, Shahinoor Nargis and Aparna Paul. The 13 cases filed in connection with the protests at DU and other educational institutions saw 36 people, including four DU teachers, accused of having roles in the August rioting. Police have already arrested 12 of the listed accused persons including DU teachers Anwar Hossain and Harun-or-Rashid. bdnews24.com/p
